 SERENA Williams has pulled out of the Italian Open starting on Monday due to an Achilles injury, the former world number one confirmed on Saturday. “I regretfully must withdraw from The Internazionali BNL d’Italia due to an Achilles strain,” Williams, a four-times winner in Rome, said in a statement https://www.wtatennis.com/news/1824796/achilles-injury-forces-serena-out-of-rome. “I’m so humbled by the continuous support from my fans in Rome and I look forward to making my return soon.” Double Wimbledon champion Petra Kvitova, 2019 U.S. Open champion Bianca Andreescu and top-ranked Ash Barty have also pulled out of the tournament.